reviews.review_text: We came for food on an evening theyre were lined out the door. The service was still extremely fast all things considered and everything was fresh with no errors in the order. The food was hot, fresh, and delicious. The portion sizes is good value for the money.  We ordered the Fried Tofu, the Double Decker, and some beverages.

Very great food. Tried out the double fried chicken and bulgogi beef fries. Not too sweet either on the sauces which is good. The bulgogi beef portion was a little lacking, but does taste good. The service was also great. One of the lady cashiers was very polite and served with a smile which is nice. Good recommend Note: the waffle fries with the chicken burger was a side order.

Wow, Chicken World has been put on notice. If youre trying to decide between the 2, this is definitely the one you want. I just had a chicken sandwich with a whole gigantic chicken breast in it. It was tender and spicy and came with delicious waffle cut fries, and I had a beer with it, all in a lovely diner with air conditioning and great ambiance.  I would love a bigger selection of local beer but on the rest I have no notes. Well done!

Visited today for late lunch. I had the best chicken sandwich I have had recently (based on my personal experience). The chicken inside the sandwich was juicy, crunch and well seasoned. The sauce and the slaw worked really well together. We ordered the OG hot chicken, hot and sweet honey garlic, and kids tenders. I personally liked the honey garlic sandwich more but the OG was also really tasty. Waffles fries were great too with a good portion size. Their house mayo was also delicious. Most of all, the lady who received our order was  so kind, attentive and friendly. The service was beyond 10/10. She even came to check how our food was and also to kindly interact with our son. Such a sweet gesture. The only criticism I have was that it was a bit cold in the restaurant. Got a tall can of beer with the chicken sammy, and this meal was so satisfying. Definitely going on my favourite restaurant list. Kid-friendliness: Kids tenders, great portion and flavour.

By far the best fried chicken Ive ever had. Truly special, spectacular, wow I was amazed at how chicken can be, the texture is incredible. Been there several times and reliable every times. Pro tip: the sweet potatoes are great but dont travel well, recommending regular fries if delivering.
Amazing food great flavors but the service and hospitality is even BETTER! Special shoutout to Sue and Sunny highly recommend Frying Pan for their amazing fried chicken and service!

Great food for takeout! I used to eat at the food truck when I worked downtown and the restaurant continues to provide the same excellent quality! The chicken is juicy and customized to your spice level, and there is a good selection of items. One of my favorite places to order from if I feel like eating chicken. Highly recommend the Dirty Hot Chicken Fries if you fancy a comfort meal.

We went 2 days in a row because i told my niece about it and she wanted to go. The staff are very friendly, the chicken was crunchy and moist, and the waffles fries were crispy.  The whole meal was scrumptious.  I would highly recommend this place to everyone.
Must try! The Best chicken burgers!! Love their rice dishes and my kids love their pancakes! YUM Recommended dishes

I cant explain how awesome this place is.  The girls that work here are so lovely.  They are so happy and great ladies. The food is absolutely amazing.  We ordered the mild hot chicken sandwich, the double decker medium chicken sandwich, smoked beef bulgogi fries, hot chicken sandwich, and a fried tofu bowl.  Everything we ordered was beyond expectations.  The food came fast, fresh and hot.  I think it was one the best chicken places I have ever had.  I cant wait to go again.
Absolutely the best chicken burger I have ever had!!! Try the double decker and add an egg to make it a family affair!

I heard about this place after reading about it in an article where they claimed their chicken sandwiches were among the best in the world. Being a crispy chicken sandwich connoisseur, I had to fond out for myself. I was a little bummed to be told they were out of Thigh meat when we got there as chicken Thigh is superior to breast in every way, but I understand that sometimes you run out of things. I ordered the spicy sandwich and the bulgogi fries. When you order, you can choose the spice level. I chose the second from hottest option. It was not spicy in the slightest, but damn was it delicious. Easily in the top 5 crispy chickens Ive had. The fries were absolutely glorious. I dont know what was in the sauces and toppings but I just about ordered another order of them. If you go here, go all the way spicy if youre into that kind of thing and dont sleepon the bulgogi fries. Parking: Pay parking in a lot out back Wheelchair accessibility: Its a one level building asily accessible by wheelchair.

Update: The Double Decker, Finally!! I got to taste their amazing Chicken Sandwich again since they moved from Gastown and their food truck doesnt come to Port Moody but thats okay. I will still come! Worth the travel from Coquitlam! :) Old Review: Best Fried Chicken!! Love their food truck and love the restaurant! Cant go wrong with any of their Chicken Burgers! I really liked the Waffle Fries with the House Mayo!! Definitely try the Lemonades too!

It is 100% the best fried chicken and waffle fries I had before. It is crunchy and flavorful. Dine in is definitely the best to eat them hot. Burger can get soggy if you choose for take out but dine in is awesome. The lemonade is also worth a try.

Best time yesterday trying almost everything on their dine out Vancouver menu. All the food was super yummy, we had tons of leftovers and the 2 waitresses were awesome. We will definitely be back to try everything else! And next time we will try the cheese sauce!!
I ate it with my family and it was really delicious. Especially, the chicken is really crispy and the French fries are delicious. The staff were kind and satisfied. You should try it

First of all, I looooved how they wrapped every single drink to protect them on the delivery process. Second of all, take the spiciness seriously! The hot is really hot! I liked the quality of the food and the generous portion sizes. Absolutely one of my favourite places.

The food is absolutely amazing. I love the waffle fries and chicken tenders! Everything we ordered was beyond expectations.  The food came fast, fresh and hot.  I think it was one the best chicken places I have ever had.  I cant wait to go again!!

Wow. Really yummy Korean food and chicken burgers. I wish I could eat this every day, but one has to workout half day to burn the amount of caleries. Not a negative point for frying pan, though! The double chicken burger is great to taste two types of coating, but its very messy to eat!   Id go with single one next time.

Went here yesterday with some friends. I have to say the service was amazing! Very friendly and always quick to help. The food was amazing, Ive been to a lot of fried chicken places in BC, and this was one of the best (top 3). Portion size huge, and the Sandos are tasty (we tried the honey garlic and original. Waffle fries are a great choice, bulgogi style is the best. Lastly get the pink lemonade over blue. Tastier. Will definitely come back here again

Excellent service! Truly some of the best I ve had in the City. The food was 4 star worthy, but the service brought this up to a 10. The hot tacos were pretty good, and so were the fries (Texas cut and super crispy).

My son heard of this place so we decided to check it out. The staff here was very attentive and friendly. They were a pleasure. The food was unreal, you could not get better hot chicken anywhere. I also love how you can order your meal how hot you want it. This place is great, I would recommend this to everyone!!

GREAT fried chicken burger. The spicy one was a little too spicy for me. If you are a     (person not good with handling spicy foods) like I am, go for the regular one. Very delicious chicken burger. I remember my eyes widened the first time I tried their burger out of their food truck. :-)

The food is as good as ever. Ive enjoyed their food since they were a food truck. Super tender and juicy, fresh ingredients and it doesnt feel like fastfood as they take the time to craft each meal for you. 5/5 for food, however they could improve the sitting area as it feels a bit empty and cold.
My favorite chicken burger!! I want to eat it every day. They are sweet and taste the best in Vancouver. I really love this fresh and healthy spicy burger. Tacos are also delicious.

Loved this place!  The service was very very friendly and kind. The food was the perfect recommendation! I got the Hot & Sweet Honey Garlic with waffle fries. The fries were a little overcooked for my liking but 100% recommend!
It would be very difficult to beat this spicy fried chicken burger. Can choose your spice, or no spice. Medium was just a touch of fire. Looks gigantic at first but was easy to eat.
Soo was so sweet and kind! Fantastic spot for fried chicken goodness. I left very happy   I love all the different spice levels and the chicken was fried to perfection. Must try!
Delicious fried chicken sandwiches, crispy, crunchy and juicy.  The waffles fries and yam fries were perfectly crispy.   just as good as their food truck
Good fried chicken sandwiches and the fries are decent, good portions...

Amazing food - burgers and fries had such good flavours! Staff were soo lovely and the interiors were fab too! Wish there was a slightly broader drink selection but everything else more than made up for it. Will definitely be returning !

Finally Fryingpan  has a brick & mortar location. Ive been a regular at their food truck and now Im super excited for the restaurant. Hands down they are the best fried chicken spot in the city. Apart from the usually delicious sandwiches, they have added the double decker to the list which is two boneless fried chicken thighs(one coated in a sweet soy sauce and the other in a hot yang nyeon sauce), cheese, lettuce and house mayo stacked between two toasted buns. The sandwiches are huge and delicious. They also do Chicken bites tossed in a sauce. I love the ones in hot yang nyeon sauce. Try the Bacon cheese fries as well. You cannot go wrong with it. Cannot wait to try other stuff on the new menu
The bulgogi fries were so good. The chicken sandwiches are also good, but the fries... I almost wanted to tell our waiter how much I loved them.
Friendly service and the food is another level! I will definitely come back

By far the best chicken burger I have ever tried... I used to wait in line for over an hour to eat at their food truck Am so happy   I can sit at a restaurant and enjoy the delicious sandwich If u r visiting Vancouver this is a must place to eat at. 10 stars. Size The sandwich is a very good size enough to fill up a food junkie like my self

I love Korean Fried Chicken and this place has a really cool take on a 80s diner, chicken burgers, chicken and waffles, etc. They mix and match cool flavors, and perhaps even better is the atmosphere. The people working there genuinely looked like they were having fun and they were so friendly and helpful. I want to try every item on the menu and the prices are pre Covid prices - e.g. great value for money. I totally recommend checking them out! :) Parking: Limited number of street parking spots down side streets. Better to walk or bike or transit Wheelchair accessibility: Its wheelchair accessible. Ground floor entrance.
Love this place. Crispy delicious chicken and waffle fries. The lovely Korean ladies are always friendly and smiling. Highly recommended

Amazing food!   They play hard with their spicy levels. If you are not quite sure how comfortable you are with spicy food, ask for your spicy sauce a side  . The tables are distant from each other. You can have a safe meal keeping social distance. Their pick up system is also working well.

Had the Korean Mozza Chicken sandwich, and it was the best chicken sandwich Ive had in memory. Interesting fusion of different cuisines that work great! Food is well prepared and the staff were friendly.
Delicious Korean style fried chicken in all sorts of presentations. Their burger is to die for. Close to English Bay. Absolutely delicious Wheelchair accessibility: No step entrance, wide door-frame

Ordered this on UberEats and it was absolutely amazing Double Decker Sandwich: The buns were very soft and pillow-y but still retained their shape! Very nice. The lettuce was oh so crisp. The 2 thighs were the best part of course. Very tender and juicy, it was like biting into chicken flavored pillows. Mozzarella Skirt Chicken Taco: The shell was really crisp and the mozzarella skirt added a lot of depth to the taco, although the cheeseyness of it can be overwhelming for some. The chicken tender in the tacos were great of course. 10/10 would recommend This is best chicken
The best fried chicken burger in metro Vancouver. Also don t miss to order their dirty hot chicken fries. Great food and amazing service. Deserves every penny.

Came here in the evening. The service was extremely friendly and efficient. Wait time could have been shorter as I did wait over 10 minutes for tacos, but once I got them, they seemed very, very fresh and hot. Flavourful and crunchy. Will be returning next time I visit English Bay!!

I have been wanting to try this place for long and I am glad I did now!!! The food is out of this world.... the best fried chicken I have ever had!!! The portion size is great and presentation is nice. Very nice staff with welcoming smile and great service. Highly recommend this place if visiting English Bay Beach!!!

We come here frequently and it never disappoints! While the food is delicious, the service is impeccable. Everyone is always so friendly and welcoming, which is a big reason we keep returning! Highly recommend.

The food here is exceptional. Tasty, fresh, tender and juicy chicken   We order take out. The dirty fries and the rice bowls have been our regular go to meals.   Also - Omfg! This is my new favourite!!! I just had the mild spicy fried chicken and it s delicious   and boneless!!!
I dont normally review places is bussin. Happy hour 3-5 $8.99 Chicken Sandwich that are huge. I got 2 and Im satisfied.
This is by far the best fried chicken sandwich/burger I have ever tried. Holy smokes... Worth every penny. I will be back soon. (Incredible service too!)

Everything is delicious. We had the double decker chicken burger and the triple cheeser. You better come hungry, because everything is BIG. Definitely worth paying this place a visit if you are in town.
Chicken sandwich heaven (tenders are also excellent). Ate here 4 times in the space of 3 weeks including my last meal in Vancouver before heading back to Melbourne.

Great burgers! Their extra hot isn t suuuper hot but you can still feel it. Really nice environment inside. Great food. Awesome service. The best part? They write little notes for you on the takeout bag and receipt! They serve HALAL CHICKEN. Parking is a little hard to find but do-able.

The best Korean Chicken Burgers i ever tried,   at Frying Pan in the heart of Gastown you will find great service,  the host as the server so happy and friendly they were on top to give you the best I definitely will go back keep it up girls
came in about 40 minutes before closing and they were really nice about it. the food was delicious and the girls were super nice and accommodating to my requests!! please visit
Best fried chicken sandwich in town!! Had it with a side of waffle fries. I am hooked and cant wait to eat it again!
Best burger ever in town! Chicken breast in burger is juicy and tender. My stomach is not really comfy with burgers but not this one.
Stopped by for lunch. Great fried chicken sandwich and smoked beef fries! Good local beers/ciders too.
Must try! Awesome fried chicken dishes..

Food was perfectly fried and arrived neatly packaged. The battered chicken breast on the sandwich was crispy and juicy as well as quite flavorful. I ordered the mild heat level which had a bit of spice to it but not so much that I couldnt enjoy the sandwich which was great. The slaw, mayo, and pickles all complimented everything well. Im putting it up there among the best fried chicken sandwiches in town. The waffle fries were how one imagines they should always be, slightly crispy on the outside but soft in the middle. Perfect for dipping sauce which the order did come with (mayo based chipotle style) and I also ordered a side of honey mustard. Will certainly try them again and explore other menu items.
Great chicken burgers.  The double chicken thigh burger is absolutely delicious its a must try for anyone who is a fan of chicken burgers.     !!!
Was dying to try this restaurant and their chicken sandwiches did not disappoint. Great service. Decent prices.

This is the best place to get crispy juicy chicken with your choice of sandwich, tacos or rice bowl.  This restaurant is known for Nashville Chicken with Korean twist. It s a flavour bomb.  Great thing is you can choose the level of spice in the menu as you order. We got Kimchi Rice Bowl, Hot Chicken Rice Bowl with amazing side dishes and their best seller Original Hot Crunch Chicken (thigh or breast)Sandwich with side dish of Waffle Fries or Yam Fries. Everything we got were perfect. This is a self-serve restaurant. The place is nice, clean and has good vibes  . The staff are nice and friendly. I highly recommend this wonderful place.
Amazing extra spicy Korean-style fried chicken sandwiches!
I went there about a week ago with no expectations, and I was surprised by how good their food was. So here I am, ordering chicken again. Staff members were extremely nice (not in an annoying way).
Amazing burgers and amazing service !! Vegetarian options: They have a lot of tofu options for vegan people as well Food : 5/5 |

This was my first time at the brick and mortar location. I am just as impressed as when I have visited their truck. Perfectly cooked chicken...spice and sweetness levels compliment each other so well. I had the OG sandwich and my gf had the Hot and Sweet Honey Garlic. Huge sandwiches, time to walk it off!
Great service great food! Best chicken place to go in English Bay Food
The chicken was so good and crispy, I loved the vibe there, the staff were super friendly and nice. Definitely coming back
It honors its name, great place for fried food lovers. Although we only ordered the poutine, it was really good, and I know the chicken is also great.
This is my to go place for chicken in town. It used to be the best food truck and now is the best restaurant.  Great food and sweet staff.
Excellent food and excellent service by every employee at the restaurant. Excellent value and we will return for dine in or take away.
Service and food are both incredible, food came out pretty quickly, flavours were great and the staff were super friendly
The best burgers and fries. So delicious. This place is a gem.
The food taste is totally worth it. You should definitely try it!

We were on vacation in Vancouver and found this place. And what can I say - it was so delicious!   defiantly one of the best chicken burger what I ever had! I fully recommend this place! Nice staff and delicious food!
Waffle Hot Chicken is delicious   would also highly recommend the Yam Fries! 10/10

Delicious chicken sandwich and their dirty fries are the best. I get them on my Friday to kick off the weekend right! Im updating my review to include my utmost gratitude to the staff at The Frying Pan for their care and dedication in providing their patrons the best product and service possible. I keep coming back for more because its always delicious and the servers are very kind and professional, and that consistency is hard to find. Thank you so much. I hope this place gets the recognition it deserves soon!
The burgers are very good, quality chicken and spicy sauce love it! Service was perfect Around 20$ burger + fries!
This place was too fire not to review. Had the mozzarella cheese skirt chicken tacos and waffle fries, with sides of sour cream, a jalapeno cheese sauce, and the 911 sauce. Perfect.

Best dining experience of my life!! The food was amazing and the portions were great. The staff was amazing and the restrooms were very clean as well. My boyfriend and I got the hot chicken dirty fries to share and the staff additionally brought us more chicken to add since they believed it wasnt enough and also a sauce dip on the house. I loved everything about this place! Considering we were tourist and had zero recommendations of where to go Im glad we ended up here

I love this place, the chicken is really moist with a good crunch. The new chicken bites they have are fantastic. I dont know if the owners read these reviews, but bring back the regular fries! They were the best in the city. The waffle fries get too soggy.
Foods are awesome and staffs are so kind!

They have the best chicken. It s perfectly done and very flavoursome. All the menu it s are excellent. Especially the chicken tacos and the bulgogi fries. They also have excellent service with the most courteous staff who always take good care of you and make sure you have a great overall experience. Highly recommend!

Ordered my food online, first time trying The Frying Pan. When I arrived the staff were very welcoming and promptly asked for my name for the order, within minutes I had my food and was out the door. I got the Dirty Hot Chicken Fries, everything in the meal was cooked perfectly, and the flavour was great. Best takeout meal I ve had in a while. Will definitely be returning!
Oh so delicious chicken. The waffle fries with fried chicken are wonderful. The spicy chicken burger is my favourite in the city. I would eat here more if my stomach was big enough!

Frying Pan is my go to fried chicken spot. Amazing fried chicken sandwiches with lots of options for spice and flavours. Dirty fries and tacos are also top notch! The food holds up even when delivered all the way to East Van. My colleagues and I used to go to their food truck every Monday, and theyve catered a few work functions for us, too. The staff have always been super friendly and attentive to allergy requests!
So glad Frying Pan is within walking distance from my house now. The staff are incredibly friendly and the food is AWESOME. Great selection of good, including dips (big fan of sauces!)
Satisfy your cravings with Frying Pans drool-worthy smoked beef bulgogi fries and hot chicken tacos! Everything was made perfectly, especially the bulgogi! Once you start going here, you wont stop.
I have been very excited to try this place from all of the great reviews. It was even better than I anticipated. Food 10/10 Service 10/10
Really good food !!! One of the best burger I ever ate.

I love fried chicken and will go out of my way to find the best in town. It used to be another place on Commercial drive but not anymore. Frying pans chicken is the best quality I ve had and is cooked to perfection. Add that to the seasoning used and you get the perfect recipe chicken for all of their dishes. Had the tacos, dirty fries and the burger - all were exceptional.  The restaurant itself is new in an old space so needs some interior design, I hope they can get to that soon to make it feel more lively.  Some dim lighting, wall art, a cool bar and some current music in the background would be the perfect touch - so much potential. For now, go for the food as you won t find a better bird.

Long term fan of the food truck and was very excited when my wife brought me to this restaurant. It did not disappoint. My wife had the Hot Garlic chicken burger (but without the heat) and I had the Hot chicken burger 911 hot. We both also had waffle fries. My wife said her burger was great and I really enjoyed mine, if you enjoy hot food I would definitely recommend it. 911 was hotter than I had in the past from the food truck (I dont think it was available from there at this heat at the time) but I would definitely have it again. As always the chicken was juicy and full of flavour. The waffle fries had some great flavour too. Service was great, very friendly and attentive staff. We also loved the aesthetic of the restaurant.
OMG!! Everything is super delicious!! Can t wait to come back!!

I just want to say a big thank you to the servers who go above and beyond to make the restaurant visit so enjoyable. I rarely find Korean restaurants with good service but this place is exceptional. The fried chicken sandwich is crazy good  it is juicy and the quality of the meat is A+. I love this place so much . I wish you guys were also open during weekday lunch. I am already thinking of my next visit. I wish this business nothing but the best. The food is 20/10. Absolutely delicious!
Definitely the best fried chicken sandwich in Vancouver! The fries are extra crispy.
Superb experience! Best chicken on Denman! Can t be missed!

Let me start by saying that I never leave reviews on anything and I felt absolutely compelled to share my experience at Frying Pan. My boyfriend and I are from Toronto so we have our share of good food but this is some of the best food we ve had in Vancouver, and Toronto as well! The fried chicken sandwiches were delicious, the waffle fries were cooked perfectly and the service we received was absolutely outstanding. Everything came out super quickly and we truly enjoyed our time there from start to finish. We ll definitely be back the next time we re in Vancouver!
Best fried chicken ever! I love their food and I am glad that they are here in West End! My go to is Hot and sweet sandwich and Pa dak sandwich!!

This was the absolute best fried chicken sandwich I have ever had. Super surprised to see not many reviews of this place, because it was unreal. The service was great, the ladies working there today were very friendly and helpful. Im a huge foodie, and with so many restaurants in Vancouver to try you have to be outstanding for me to return again. This is one I know I will be back to many times. I will be recommending this to anyone I know visiting Vancouver!

Got two chicken sandwiches and hot and honey was my favourite. One of the best chicken sandwiches I ve tried. So juicy in the inside and crispy on the outside. Right amount of sauce and toppings fit well. I am going to come back often

Watched a video on YouTube of the owners talking about how they wanted to open up a restaurant but didn t have the means to, so they opened up a food truck instead. Looked them up on google maps and noticed they did open up a restaurant, so I decided I had to go there and try out their food! I went with the famous hot chicken sandwich with 911 sauce. Added on fried egg, bacon and cheese. It was delicious! Highly recommended! If you re in the neighbourhood, you most definitely want to check out this restaurant!
